<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Meiring Denies Asking Modise for Interdict </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Meiring Denies Asking Modise for Interdict </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB1706163894 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 1100 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB1706163894 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A spokesman for the Ministry of Defense, Dr. Das 
Herbst, has denied allegations of a power struggle between the 
minister of defense, Mr. Joe Modise, and the chief of the 
National Defense Force, General George Meiring. Dr. Herbst was 
reacting to a report in the WEEKLY MAIL &amp; GUARDIAN in which 
it 
was alleged that General Meiring had asked Mr. Modise to request 
and interdict against the newspaper. General Meiring apparently 
warned Mr. Modise that the government could be harmed if the 
names of spies in the ANC were revealed. The newspaper says it 
has forced the army to confirm the names of 47 former and 
current employees of the Directorate of Covert Intelligence. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

