<H3> <TI>   Justice Minister: Truth Commission To Go Ahead </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Justice Minister: Truth Commission To Go Ahead </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB2006090394 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 0500 GMT 20 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB2006090394 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Justice Minister Dullah Omar says plans for a Truth 
and Reconciliation Commission will go ahead despite opposition 
expressed by the commissioner of police. Police Commissioner 
General Johan van der Merwe has submitted a document to the 
safety and security minister in which he warns that the 
commission could bring about the downfall of top ANC members. 
  Johannesburg's BUSINESS DAY newspaper quoted Mr. Omar as 
saying that the government was not worried about this 
possibility and that it was no reason to suppress the truth. He 
said the ANC accepted that its members might have to appear 
before the commission. 

</TEXT>

