BFN 

  [Text] The integration of Umkhonto we Sizwe [Spear of the 
Nation; MK -- ANC armed wing] into the National Defense Force is 
reported to be going smoothly now, and more than 3,000 members 
of the former armed wing of the ANC will begin their training at 
Wallmansthall near Pretoria on Monday. The integration of MK 
into the defense force will cost an estimated 132 million rands. 
Negotiations on the integration of APLA [Azanian People's 
Liberation Army] are under way at the moment. 

