<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   ANC Maintains Rejection of Natal Provincial Capital </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    ANC Maintains Rejection of Natal Provincial Capital </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    NP Urges Responsibility in Handling Issue </H4>

<F P=102> MB1806064294 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 0500 GMT 18 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB1806064294 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The National Party [NP] has warned that 
KwaZulu-Natal could suffer untold harm to its economy unless the 
question of a capital for the region is handled responsibly. 
This follows reports of an ANC plan to boycott a provincial 
legislature meeting in Ulundi. Mr. Tino Volker of the NP called 
for a special sitting of the provincial legislature to appoint 
an advisory committee on the site for a capital. 
  Meanwhile, the ANC has confirmed it will boycott the next 
sitting of the KwaZulu-Natal Legislature which is scheduled to 
be held in Ulundi at the end of this month. The ANC said it was 
politically wrong to hold the meeting in the IFP stronghold. 

</TEXT>

