<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   ANC To Begin Restructuring of Headquarters Staff </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    ANC To Begin Restructuring of Headquarters Staff </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB1806100594 Johannesburg WEEKEND STAR in English 18-19 Jun 
94 p 1 </F>

<F P=103> MB1806100594 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg WEEKEND STAR </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by labor correspondent Jovial Rantao] </F>
  [Text] The ANC has advised most of its head office staff to 
seek work elsewhere or opt for voluntary retrenchment as jobs 
will be lost when the organisation begins restructuring on 
October 1. 
  ANC sources said party secretary-general Cyril Ramaphosa 
held 
a staff meeting yesterday -- the second in two weeks -- at which 
he spelt out the situation. 
  Documents leaked to WEEKEND STAR show that the decision to 
reorganise the party's head office, which employs more than 
1,000 people, was taken on Tuesday by the ANC's national working 
committee. 
  The committee decided that voluntary retrenchment, at the 
discretion of the organisation, would be effected on July 1. 
Retrenchment packages of four months' salary plus an amount for 
each year of service would be offered. 
  Staff who did not opt for voluntary retrenchment and were 
not 
appointed to new positions would be retrenched on October 1 with 
two months' salary plus an amount for each year of service. 
  Employees at the ANC's headquarters said yesterday that they 
were saddened by the development. Most had hoped to be 
integrated into the public service. 
  Ramaphosa would not comment yesterday. A news briefing would 
be organised next week to outline the reorganisation, he said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
