<H3> <TI>   Consultations Termed `Positive' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Consultations Termed `Positive' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB2006090494 Luanda Radio Nacional Network in Portuguese 
0600 GMT 20 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB2006090494 </F>
<F P=104>  Luanda Radio Nacional Network </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Alioune Blondin Beye, UN special representative in 
Angola, has returned to Lusaka after visiting Huambo and Luanda 
for consultations with UNITA [National Union for the Total 
Independence of Angola] and government leaders at the weekend. 
In Huambo, Beye briefed Savimbi and his closest aides on the 
positive steps that have been taken at the talks. He guaranteed 
that some 90 percent of the hurdles have already been overcome. 
He conveyed similar views to Angolan President of the Republic 
Jose Eduardo dos Santos. UN sources in Luanda noted that Beye 
received a positive response from UNITA and government. 

</TEXT>

