<F P=100> SOUTHERN AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Angola </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further on Clashes </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further on Clashes </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB1806092594 Luanda Radio Nacional Network in Portuguese 
0600 GMT 18 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB1806092594 </F>
<F P=104>  Luanda Radio Nacional Network </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The military situation in the city of Kuito remains 
unaltered. Clashes are under way and the National Union for the 
Total Independence of Angola [UNITA] forces are being reinforced 
with contingents from Huambo and Cuando Cubango Provinces. Many 
people are still dying in the Bie capital. The atmosphere of 
war in Kuito is characterized by gunpowder, blood and hunger, 
and the main victims are civilians whom the UNITA rebels have 
decided to strike with their Machiavellian actions with the aim 
of taking over the city at all costs. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

