<F P=100> SOUTHERN AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Angola </F>
<H3> <TI>   UNITA Intensifies Shelling </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UNITA Intensifies Shelling </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB1806203594 Luanda Radio Nacional Network in Portuguese 
1900 GMT 18 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB1806203594 </F>
<F P=104>  Luanda Radio Nacional Network </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] The National Union for the Total Independence of 
Angola [UNITA] has once again begun to intensify the shelling of 
the Kuito and Kunje in Bie Province. About 200 wounded people 
could die in the coming five days because of a lack of medicines 
and medical care. [passage omitted] 
  What is more, Jonas Savimbi's men continue to shell the town 
of Tchindjenje in Huambo Province. The aim is to take 
Tchindjenje District, but government troops are preventing the 
rebels' advance. Apart from shelling the town, UNITA is laying 
mines on paths leading to peasants' farms. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

