<H3> <TI>   Zairian Involvement in Conflict Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Zairian Involvement in Conflict Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB1806164394 Luanda Radio Nacional Network in Portuguese 
1200 GMT 18 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB1806164394 </F>
<F P=104>  Luanda Radio Nacional Network </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Zairian involvement in the Angolan conflict 
continues. In Malanje Province Zairian citizens are fighting 
alongside the National Union for the Total Independence of 
Angola [UNITA]. Our correspondent Francisco Kuringana has 
further details. 
  A total of 48 civilians who fled from areas controlled by 
the 
rebels today presented themselves to the government forces 
stationed in Quemba area, 14 km east of Malanje. These 
civilians said Zairian citizens not only fight alongside UNITA 
forces but also carry out trade activities in Caculama District 
and accord logistical assistance to Jonas Savimbi's men. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

