<H3> <TI>   UNITA To Release British, French Aid Workers </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UNITA To Release British, French Aid Workers </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1706190794 Lisbon Radio Renascenca in Portuguese to Europe 
1800 GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1706190794 </F>
<F P=104>  Lisbon Radio Renascenca </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] UNITA [National Union for the Total Independence of 
Angola] will allow the release of all foreign nationals, 
particularly those of French and British nationality, held as 
hostages since Wednesday [15 June] in Huambo. UNITA insists 
their exit from Huambo has to be well organized. UNITA 
Spokesman Jorge Valentim made the announcement when reacting 
today to disagreement between his organization and the United 
Nations relating to the situation of 56 foreign nationals who 
have been held in Huambo under unexplained circumstances. 
Huambo has been under UNITA control since March of last year. 

</TEXT>

