<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-AFR-94-118 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  19 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> SOUTHERN AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Mozambique </F>
<H3> <TI>   Renamo Official Says No Problems in Reintegration </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Renamo Official Says No Problems in Reintegration </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB1906190594 Maputo Radio Mozambique Network in Portuguese 
1730 GMT 19 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB1906190594 </F>
<F P=104>  Maputo Radio Mozambique Network </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Francisco Rupansana, co-chairman of the National 
Commission for Territorial Administration on the Mozambique 
National Resistance's [Renamo] side, says that there are no 
major problems in the process of reintegrating areas under 
Renamo control. Francisco Rupansana told Radio Mozambique in 
Chimoio that the government must carry out an efficient 
coordination work to once and for all resolve the problem of 
double administration. In Macossa District in Manica Province, 
Rupansana attended the signing of a contract by Renamo 
administrator Antonio Pedemo for the reintegration of the 
district in the country's single administration. 

</TEXT>

