<F P=101> Somalia </F>
<H3> <TI>   SNA Condemns Upsurge in Terrorism </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    SNA Condemns Upsurge in Terrorism </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA1906203594 (Clandestine) Radio Mogadishu Voice of the 
Great Somali People in Somali 1700 GMT 19 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA1906203594 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Radio Mogadishu Voice of the 
Great Somali People </F>

<F P=105>  Somali </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A spokesman for the Somali National Alliance, SNA, 
has said that these days armed terrorist groups are emerging. 
The terrorists, which are supported and spearheaded by foreign 
and Somali individuals, commit murders and kidnap innocent 
people. The spokesman described the terrorist acts as 
anti-human rights and anti-international terrorism laws. He 
said the SNA was strongly opposed to any form of terrorism and 
supported international agreements on terrorism and banditry. 
  The spokesman went on to say that the SNA was making 
comprehensive investigations to bring to justice those 
responsible for the banditry and kidnappings which had been 
committed in the country this year. In the investigations, the 
SNA had already got answers to several terrorist incidents and 
the identities of those responsible had been submitted to 
international organizations dealing with the fight against 
banditry and terrorism. The SNA spokesman said the Somali 
people had just adopted the course of unity and coexistence. He 
finally called on peace-loving Somali people to jointly counter 
those opposed to peace who were busy committing terrorism to 
harm peaceful coexistence. 

</TEXT>

