<F P=100> EAST AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Tanzania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Militias Causing Insecurity in Refugee Camps </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Militias Causing Insecurity in Refugee Camps </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA1806161094 (Clandestine) Radio Muhabura in English to 
Rwanda 1100 GMT 18 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA1806161094 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Radio Muhabura </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The refugee camp at Benaco in Tanzania, is faced 
with lack of order and security caused by notorious militias 
like Gatete who have assumed the leadership of the camp. The 
president of Medecins sans Frontieres, (Bernard Grandjean), said 
that people have been killed and activities paralyzed in the 
camp. Journalists and humanitarian workers have been chased out 
of the camp by the militias. The militias also harass and stop 
people who want to come back to Rwanda and instead argue with 
them to stay in camps in Tanzania so that they can be trained 
and armed to attack Rwandan Patriotic Front forces in Rwanda. 
The Tanzanian authorities and the UNHCR should come to the 
rescue of the people in this refugee camp and also be able to 
control the activities of the militias who take the law into 
their own hands. 

</TEXT>

