<H3> <TI>   Court Rejects Treason Charge Against Activist </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Court Rejects Treason Charge Against Activist </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AB1706171894 Paris AFP in English 1521 GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> AB1706171894 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Lagos, June 17 (AFP) -- A court here Friday [17 
June] rejected a charge of treason against Beko Ransome-Kuti, 
national president of the Campaign for Democracy, but he was 
refused immediate bail. 
  Ransome-Kuti, who was arrested on June 9, heads an umbrella 
group for about 40 pro-democracy and human rights organisations. 
  The Federal High Court rejected on technical grounds a 
charge 
of treasonable felony and intent to remove the head of state by 
unconstitutional means. 
  Consideration of a bail application was postponed until 
Tuesday. 
  Ransome-Kuti has been spearheading a campaign to remove the 
military junta from power. 

</TEXT>

