<F P=100> CENTRAL AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Zaire </F>
<H3> <TI>   Opposition Criticizes </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Opposition Criticizes </PHRASE></F></HT>


<TEXT>
French   Intervention in Rwanda 

<F P=102> AB2006150094 Paris AFP in French 0944 GMT 20 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> AB2006150094 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>
BFN 

  [Text] Kinshasa, 20 Jun (AFP) -- The Union for Democracy 
and Social Progress [UDPS], the main radical opposition party 
led by Etienne Tshisekedi, today strongly criticized any French 
intervention in Rwanda. In a communique published by the 
radical opposition media, UDPS said the humanitarian reasons put 
forward by France are "a mere pretext." "In reality," the 
communique said, "the French, after realizing that their 
protege, the late President Habyarimana's militia, which was 
armed and trained by them, is losing ground, are shamelessly 
preparing to give them a hand in order to recapture lost ground 
and to counterattack the democratic forces which are progressing 
in central Africa." 
  The UDPS added that France is supporting "dictatorships in 
Africa," and declared that it will hold responsible "before 
history, any Zairian who helps in undertaking any act of 
aggression against Rwanda from Zairian territory." 
  The UDPS concluded by saying that any French intervention in 
Rwanda outside the United Nations "would constitute a deliberate 
provocation against the progressive and democratic forces of 
central Africa." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

