<F P=101> Zaire </F>
<H3> <TI>   Mobutu Signs Decree Appointing New Prime Minister </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Mobutu Signs Decree Appointing New Prime Minister </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AB1706143094 Paris AFP in French 0914 GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> AB1706143094 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kinshasa, 17 Jun (AFP) -- Marshal Mobutu Sese Seko 
today signed the decree appointing the new prime minister, Kengo 
Wa Dondo, who was elected on 14 June by the High Council of the 
Republic-Transition Parliament, an official source disclosed. 
The ordinance was signed in line with the transitional 
constitution that will regulate the functioning of the Zairian 
institutions up to the adoption of the new constitution which 
will mark the advent of the Third Republic. 
  Mr. Kengo Wa Dondo's election has already been rejected by 
hardliners of the Sacred Union of the Radical Opposition [USOR] 
which supports Etienne Tshisekedi whom they consider the sole 
"legal" prime minister of Zaire. Mr. Kengo Wa Dondo belongs to 
the moderate group of the USOR led by the Union for the Republic 
and Democracy. 

</TEXT>

