<H3> <TI>   Renamo Reopens Nampula Registration Centers </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Renamo Reopens Nampula Registration Centers </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB2106093494 Maputo Radio Mozambique Network in Portuguese 
0800 GMT 21 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB2106093494 </F>
<F P=104>  Maputo Radio Mozambique Network </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Mozambique National Resistance [Renamo] has 
allowed the reopening of two electoral registration centers in 
areas under its control in Nampula Province's Malema District -- 
namely, (Nicuassula) and (Leia). Benedito Vasco Verde, chairman 
of Nampula's Provincial Electoral Commission, says the delay in 
the reopening of the centers was due to a lack of transport. 
With the reopening of the two centers all Renamo-controlled 
areas in Nampula Province can now be registered. 

</TEXT>

