  [Excerpt] The government troops' assembly area in Boane, 
Maputo Province, was closed down today. The Boane Assembly Area 
is the first to be closed down within the framework of the 
implementation of the General Peace Accord. Present at the 
closing ceremony were officials from the government, the 
Mozambique National Resistance, and the UN Operations in 
Mozambique. The assembly area was opened last February and it 
had 1,500 troops. [passage omitted] 

