<H3> <TI>   COSATU Supports Idea of Truth Commission </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    COSATU Supports Idea of Truth Commission </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB2106081894 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 0500 GMT 21 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB2106081894 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] COSATU [Congress of South African Trade Unions] has 
rejected the criticism by the commissioner of police, General 
Johan van der Merwe, of the so-called truth commission. COSATU 
said that among other things it wanted to know who was 
responsible for the murder and disappearance of trade union 
members during the apartheid regime, and for the explosion at 
COSATU House. COSATU said that Gen. van der Merwe's criticism 
was suspect after the attempt by the head of the SANDF [South 
African National Defense Force], Gen. George Meiring, to obtain 
a court order against the publication of covert army operations. 
It is reported that the minister of justice, Mr. Dullah Omar, 
has indicated that the truth commission will go ahead despite 
Gen. van der Merwe's opposition. 

</TEXT>

