<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Proposes Political Party Amendment </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Proposes Political Party Amendment </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB2006190894 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 1600 GMT 20 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB2006190894 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] National Party [NP] leader F.W. de Klerk says the 
constitution should be amended to make provision for the 
establishment of a new party without members of parliament being 
forced to resign from their posts. 
  Speaking in a news conference in Cape Town, Mr. de Klerk 
said 
that according to the present constitution a large group within 
a political party was not permitted to break away and form a new 
party. Mr. de Klerk added that although he was in favor of 
proportional representation being retained in the new 
constitution, geographical representation should be incorporated 
as well. He also announced that the NP, until now made up of 
four provincial parties, would become one federal party. 

</TEXT>

