<H3> <TI>   PWV Selects Johannesburg as Provincial Capital </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PWV Selects Johannesburg as Provincial Capital </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB2006173594 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 1600 GMT 20 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB2006173594 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] All political parties in the PWV [Pretoria, 
Witwatersrand, Vereeniging] Provincial Legislature have 
indicated they will support the choice of Johannesburg as a 
provincial capital. The report in which a special committee 
recommends Johannesburg in preference to Pretoria or Midrand was 
tabled in the Legislature this afternoon. The Freedom Front 
said a condition for its support was that the ANC deal with the 
question of Afrikaner cultural freedom with great 
circumspection. The IFP [Inkatha Freedom Party] said it 
supported Johannesburg as a short-term choice, but that Midrand 
was more suitable in the long term. The Provincial Legislature 
is to discuss the question tomorrow. 

</TEXT>

