<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Defense Force Deployed in Umtata To Contain Mutiny </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Defense Force Deployed in Umtata To Contain Mutiny </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB2106121594 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 1100 GMT 21 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB2106121594 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The South African National Defense Force troops have 
been deployed around Umtata to contain the mutiny by Transkeian 
soldiers. A column of defense force armored vehicles has also 
been spotted traveling toward the northern Transkei where the 
Maluti Army Base is situated. More than 300 Transkeian soldiers 
have been detained for mutinous activities following the 
incident last week when troops based in Port St. Johns and 
Umtata protested about salaries and took a senior officer 
hostage. The officer was freed by troops from Eastern Province 
Command. 

</TEXT>

