<F P=100> CENTRAL AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Rwanda </F>
<H3> <TI>   RPF Continues Stance Against French Intervention </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    RPF Continues Stance Against French Intervention </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Calls on OAU To Denounce Plan </H4>

<F P=102> EA2106160094 (Clandestine) Radio Muhabura in Kinyarwanda to 
Rwanda 1015 GMT 21 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA2106160094 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Radio Muhabura </F>
<F P=105>  Kinyarwanda </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] [passage omitted] Up to now, the OAU secretary 
general has not said anything. However this is the right time 
to speak out. They should talk so that everyone's position is 
clear. It is clear that some OAU member countries still behave 
like colonized people instead of searching for the truth. These 
are for example countries which agreed to send their troops in 
the campaign to be led by France. The Rwandan Patriotic Front 
[RPF] representatives in Brussels gave them the right message: 
Please find other ways to repay the French debt, not with 
Rwandan blood. 
  The OAU agreed to sit with the leader of the killers, 
Theodore Sindikubwabo, the interim president of Rwanda. This 
has been said and forgotten but the OAU should not add one evil 
to another. The OAU should choose the right path and openly 
denounce the French aggression, because the consequences will be 
many. [passage omitted]. 

</TEXT>

