<H3> <TI>   Government Calls For Medical Aid for Refugees </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Calls For Medical Aid for Refugees </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA2106211094 Dar es Salaam Radio Tanzania External Service 
in English 1600 GMT 21 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA2106211094 </F>
<F P=104>  Dar es Salaam Radio Tanzania External Service 
in English 1600 GMT 21 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=105> English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tanzania has appealed to the international community 
for assistance in the field of medicine, to be able to cope with 
the problems caused by the influx of Rwandese refugees in the 
Kagera region. The appeal was made in Dar es Salaam by the 
prime minister and first vice president, the Honorable John 
Malecela, who said an outbreak of diarrhoea has been reported in 
Kagera region. The Honorable Malecela made the appeal during 
talks in his office in Dar es Salaam with the representative of 
the World Health Organization to Tanzania and Seychelles, Dr. 
(B. Woring), who paid him a courtesy call. The prime minister 
also appealed for help in enhancing Tanzania's ability to 
provide health centers with essential drug kits. Denmark is 
assisting Tanzania in its essential drugs program and the prime 
minister said it was Tanzania's hope that other donors would do 
the same. 

</TEXT>

