<F P=100> WEST AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Nigeria </F>
<H3> <TI>   Three Appear in Court on Treason Charges </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Three Appear in Court on Treason Charges </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AB2206083394 Lagos Radio Nigeria Network in English 0600 GMT 
22 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> AB2206083394 </F>
<F P=104>  Lagos Radio Nigeria Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Three persons -- Chief Segun Osoba, Mr. Jonah David 
Jang, and retired Air Commodore Dan Suleiman -- yesterday 
appeared before the Federal High Court [FHC] in Lagos on charges 
of treason. The chief judge of the FHC, Mr. Justice Mohamed 
Belgore, who was presiding over the case, directed that the men, 
who are on bail should not be rearrested. 
  The defense had complained that the accused persons were 
being harassed by the police and security agents. Mr. Justice 
Belgore ruled that the police or security agents should not 
interrogate, visit, or invite any of the three accused persons 
without specific order from the court, pending the determination 
of the case. He also directed that the bail of the accused 
persons should continue under the present condition till 
tomorrow when hearing of the case would continue. 
  Also, yesterday, Mr. Justice Belgore granted bail to a 
Lagos- 
based medical practitioner, Dr. Beko Ransome-Kuti, standing 
trial for treasonable felony. Dr. Ransome-Kuti was however 
asked to sign an undertaking not to commit the same offense he 
was charged with in the [words indistinct] bail. He was banned 
from addressing any gathering, issuing press statements, or 
participating in any public gathering, and he must remain within 
his locality. In addition, he will produce two sureties and pay 
a sum of 10,000 naira which would be forfeited in the event of 
nonfulfillment of the conditions. Mr. Justice Belgore stressed 
that any breach of the conditions would invalidate the bail. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

