<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Transkei Force Denies SANDF in Control of Bases </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Transkei Force Denies SANDF in Control of Bases </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB2206070194 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 0500 GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB2206070194 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Transkei Defense Force has denied that SANDF 
[South African National Defense Force] soldiers have taken over 
control of military bases in the Transkei. However, SANDF 
soldiers were deployed at bases at the Transkei's request to 
quell the mutiny. This follows rioting last week when soldiers 
in Port St. Johns and Umtata protested against low salaries and 
held a senior officer hostage. The officer commanding the SANDF 
in the Transkei, Major General Themba Matanzima, said 195 
Transkei Defense Force members were being held in connection 
with the mutiny. 

</TEXT>

