<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   PWV Premier Calls For Transfer of Powers </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PWV Premier Calls For Transfer of Powers </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB2106191294 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1656 GMT 21 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB2106191294 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Johannesburg June 21 SAPA -- PWV [Pretoria, 
Witwatersrand, Vereeniging] Premier Tokyo Sexwale on Tuesday [21 
June] warned of people turning away from the African National 
Congress government if premiers were not given their powers 
soon. Speaking after a PWV Provincial Legislature sitting at 
Nasrec [National Exhibition Center] near Soweto he said people 
were expecting him to tackle issues such as housing, health and 
education for which he needed powers stipulated in terms of the 
constitution. 
  He and his 10 MECs [members of the Executive Committee] have 
been given powers equivalent to that of the Transvaal Provincial 
Administration Executive Committee, but many other powers had 
yet to be conferred. 
  Mr Sexwale said people would seek another government if no 
progress was made because he had no power to act. Mr Sexwale 
hoped an announcement on the remaining powers would be made soon. 

</TEXT>

