<H3> <TI>   British Adviser To Help Set Up Defense Ministry </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    British Adviser To Help Set Up Defense Ministry </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB2106161794 Maseru Radio Lesotho in English 1130 GMT 21 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> MB2106161794 </F>
<F P=104>  Maseru Radio Lesotho </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A civilian adviser from the British Ministry of 
Defense, Mr. Phil Jones, has assumed his duties in Maseru in 
secondment to the Lesotho Government to assist with the 
establishment of a Ministry of Defense. According to a press 
statement released by the British High Commission in Maseru, Mr. 
Jones' duties will include guidance on procurement, the 
production of annual plans, advice on financial central systems, 
the establishment of appropriate office procedures and the 
provision of hands-on training support. Mr. Jones is expected 
to return to the United Kingdom at the end of March 1995 on 
completion of his assignment. 

</TEXT>

