<H3> <TI>   PDP Secretary General Resigns, Remains in Government </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PDP Secretary General Resigns, Remains in Government </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AB2206172594 Bamako Radiodiffusion-Television du Mali Radio 
in French 0700 GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> AB2206172594 </F>
<F P=104>  Bamako Radiodiffusion-Television du Mali Radio 
in French 0700 GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=105> French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The secretary general of the Party for Democracy and 
Progress [PDP], Mr. Boubacar Karamoko Coulibaly, has resigned 
from the party. He said in a communique that this is a 
definitive and irrevocable resignation which frees him from his 
position as party leader and militant. The communique added 
that the leaders of the PDP did not accept that Boubacar 
Karamoko Coulibaly decided to remain in the government while the 
party had decided to withdraw. 
  To remain in the government, Mr. Coulibaly, who said he 
acted 
with the best interest of the nation at heart, resigned from the 
PDP. For more details, Mr. Coulibaly will give a press briefing 
today as of 1600 at the Hotel de l'Amitie. The national and 
international media is invited to attend. 

</TEXT>

