<F P=100> WEST AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Nigeria </F>
<H3> <TI>   Abacha Advises Military To Shun `Self-Proclaimed Democrats' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Abacha Advises Military To Shun `Self-Proclaimed Democrats' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AB2306103194 Kaduna Radio Nigeria in English 0900 GMT 23 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> AB2306103194 </F>
<F P=104>  Kaduna Radio Nigeria </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Members of the Armed Forces have again been advised 
to resist attempts by disgruntled elements to cause disaffection 
and discontent in the society. Addressing a combined parade of 
Army, Air Force, and the police in Kaduna, the head of state, 
General Sani Abacha, said some misguided citizens have been 
going round barracks and military formations trying to create 
confusion. He pointed out that such people were using religious 
and tribal sentiments in an attempt to discomfort members of the 
Armed Forces. 
  The head of state, therefore, reminded members of the Armed 
Forces of their responsibility to ensure peace and stability of 
the country. Gen. Abacha then warned the soldiers to shun any 
mischievous characters manifesting themselves as politicians and 
self-proclaimed democrats. He drew their attention to the fact 
that in the event of any crisis, the soldiers would be the first 
victims. The commander in chief assured them that government was 
fully aware of the sacrifices they were making to keep the 
country together. He however warned that the present 
administration would not submit to blackmail from certain 
quarters in subverting the cause of the democratic process being 
implemented by government. 
  On the economy, Gen. Abacha acknowledged that the country 
was 
passing through a difficult period but assured that the 
government would fully implement the measures announced in this 
year's budget to bring relief. 

</TEXT>

