administration. 
  Responding, Gen. Abacha said he was in Jos to consult with 
officers and men of the 3d Armored Division on the state of the 
nation. He appealed to traditional rulers to join hands with 
the government to ensure the maintenance of peace and security 
in the state. Gen. Abacha gave an assurance that his 
administration was committed to the democratization process and 
called for cooperation from indigenes of the state. 

