<F P=100> WEST AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Nigeria </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Powers Warned Against Backing Terrorism, Disorder </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Powers Warned Against Backing Terrorism, Disorder </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AB2306091094 Lagos Radio Nigeria Network in English 0600 GMT 
23 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> AB2306091094 </F>
<F P=104>  Lagos Radio Nigeria Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Federal Government says no amount of pressure, 
internal threat, or external intimidation will force it to take 
measures that are likely to create anarchy in the country. The 
secretary to the government of the federation, Alhaji Aminu 
Saleh, stated this in Abuja last night at a reception for media 
executives. He said government was determined to put in place a 
genuine democratic government as soon as possible. 
  Alhaji Aminu advised some foreign powers against sponsoring 
terrorism and disorder in the country. He said no country 
should be allowed to impose its political ideas on the country 
since Nigeria has never imposed its ideas on any other country. 
The secretary to the government said the Constitutional 
Conference was at present the only legally constituted body to 
carry out the assignment on behalf of the people of this 
country. He said government would continue to rely on the mass 
media for an objective assessment of economic policies. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

