<F P=102>   AB2406094594 Dakar PANA in French 0913 GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> AB2406094594 </F>
<F P=104>  Dakar PANA </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Dakar, 24 Jun (APS-SEN/PANA) -- About 40 
Senegalese soldiers left Dakar this morning for Rwanda, where 
they will participate in the French humanitarian mission there, 
it was observed at the airport of the Senegalese capital. This 
first contingent, a section of the Senegalese Army, was seen off 
upon departure by Armed Forces Minister Madieng Khary Dieng. It 
will be followed by others, reliable sources stated, specifying 
that Senegal is expected to commit 300 men in the French 
operation placed under the auspices of the United Nations. 
These sources add that the Senegalese soldiers will be based at 
Goma, a town in eastern Zaire, on the border with Rwanda. 
