<H3> <TI>   Ramaphosa Seeking Constitutional Experts for Assembly </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ramaphosa Seeking Constitutional Experts for Assembly </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB2306164294 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 1500 GMT 23 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB2306164294 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Constitutional Assembly, which is to draw up 
South Africa's final constitution over the next two years, is to 
ask for nominations by the end of next month for a panel of 
constitutional experts to advise it. Constitutional Assembly 
Chairman Cyril Ramaphosa said in Cape Town it would then be able 
to start sifting through the nominations during the August 
session of Parliament. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

