<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Modise Willing to Testify Before Truth Commission </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Modise Willing to Testify Before Truth Commission </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB2506063894 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 0500 GMT 25 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB2506063894 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Defense Minister Joe Modise says he is willing to 
testify before the government's proposed commission on 
reconciliation and truth. Speaking in Cape Town, he said the 
ANC had nothing to hide and that everybody who was supposed to 
testify before the commission would do so. However, he added 
that he had said all that he needed to say in testimony to an 
internal ANC commission last year. 
  Mr. Modise was among ANC leaders named in that report as 
having perpetrated or allowed human rights abuses in ANC 
detention camps in Angola. Mr. Modise's statement is a sequel 
to a request by nine former generals of the SADF [South African 
Defense Force] and the police that senior ANC members set an 
example by giving evidence before the truth commission. The 
group, including Freedom Front Leader Constand Viljoen, is 
demanding fairness toward all parties regarding past misdeeds. 

</TEXT>

