<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    ECOMOG Foils Attempt To Destabilize Monrovia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AB2706105394 Monrovia Radio ELBC in English 0900 GMT 27 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> AB2706105394 </F>
<F P=104>  Monrovia Radio ELBC </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A joint security operation with ECOMOG [Economic 
Community of West African States Cease-Fire Monitoring] and 
local security yesterday foiled an attempt to destabilize the 
peace and security of Monrovia. The press secretary to the 
field commander of ECOMOG, Mr. Francis Akinola, confirmed the 
operation, and said [words indistinct]. According to him, 
ECOMOG, the (?state security), and the Defense Ministry [word 
indistinct] carried out a surprise dawn check on some residences 
in Paynesville, including that of Mr. Alhaji Koromah. Mr. 
Akinola told journalists that some 26,000 thousand rounds of 
ammunition, 30 assorted weapons, 18 RPG launchers, 16 RPG bombs, 
and some communication equipment were found during the 
operation. Those arrested by ECOMOG are helping the peace 
keepers in efforts to ascertain where more arms and ammunition 
may have been kept. 
  Meanwhile, ECOMOG is again calling on the public to provide 
information that will [words indistinct] in and around Monrovia. 

