<H3> <TI>   President's Widow Denies RPF Involved </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President's Widow Denies RPF Involved </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2706222394 Paris France-2 Television Network in French 
1800 GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2706222394 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris France-2 Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Hatred broke out in Rwanda and atrocious 
massacres took place because of an attack on the plane carrying 
the presidents of Rwanda and Burundi in Kigali on 6 April. 
[passage omitted] 
  A former officer [Captain Barril] is reported to have got 
hold of the black box in Kigali, where he went at the request of 
the family, who have found refuge in France, so that he could 
start all inquiries he deemed useful to find the truth about the 
attack: 
  [Begin recording] [Mrs. Habyarimana, Rwandan president's 
widow] You know, inquiries have been started, but I can tell you 
that people said straight away that the RPF [Rwanda Patriotic 
Front] was behind the attack but, since I left the country 
without knowing what people were saying, I can guarantee that 
the Rwandan army did not shoot at the president because the 
Rwandan army did not have any missiles. [end processing] 
[passage omitted] 
  The Dassault-Aviation company has just issued a 
clarification 
that goes against Captain Barril's revelations: According to 
Dassault-Aviation, there was no black box on the former Rwandan 
president's plane, a Falcon-50. 

</TEXT>

