<H3> <TI>   SNA Warns Supporters Against Incitement to `War' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    SNA Warns Supporters Against Incitement to `War' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA2706191594 (Clandestine) Radio Mogadishu Voice of the 
Great Somali People in Somali 1700 GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA2706191594 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Radio Mogadishu Voice of the 
Great Somali People </F>

<F P=105>  Somali </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A spokesman for the Somali National Alliance, SNA, 
has said that these days many troublemakers were emerging who 
were engaged in fighting in some parts of Mogadishu. The 
spokesman said personalities who signed the Nairobi peace accord 
on 24 March 1994 and other accords and who called themselves 
political leaders were fanning new hostilities and war in a bid 
to divide the Somali people. 
  The spokesman appealed to the Somali people to be on their 
guard against those causing friction aimed at bringing problems 
similar to those of the past. The spokesman said the alliance 
was opposed to the war which was being waged people against 
peace. He said the SNA was not ready to wage war against 
anybody, and appealed to its supporters to desist from taking 
Somali people's lives and committing robbery. The SNA spokesman 
concluded by saying that peace-loving Somalis should unite and 
counter those opposed to peace and coexistence. 

</TEXT>

