<H3> <TI>   National Constitutional Conference Begins in Abuja </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    National Constitutional Conference Begins in Abuja </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Taraba Delegate Replaced </H4>

<F P=102> AB2706131094 Lagos Radio Nigeria Network in English 1200 GMT 
27 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> AB2706131094 </F>
<F P=104>  Lagos Radio Nigeria Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The head of state, General Sani Abacha, has 
appointed Mr. (Saleh Abubakar) to replace Alhaji Abubakar Barde 
from Taraba State as the government's nominated delegate to the 
Constitutional Conference, which has begun today. The 
replacement of Alhaji Abubakar Barde followed information that 
he was one of those already elected to the conference. A 
statement by the secretary to the Government of the Federation, 
Alhaji Aminu Saleh, advised the new nominee to proceed to Abuja 
immediately for the conference as one of the three nominees from 
Taraba State. 

</TEXT>

