<F P=100> WEST AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Nigeria </F>
<H3> <TI>   Seven Demonstrators Injured by Gunfire in Lagos </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Seven Demonstrators Injured by Gunfire in Lagos </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AB2806120194 Paris AFP in English 1129 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> AB2806120194 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Lagos, 28 Jun (AFP) -- Seven women demonstrators 
were wounded by gunfire and hundreds of people arrested during a 
rally in support of opposition leader Moshood Abiola, the 
committee for the defence of human rights said on Tuesday [28 
June]. The women, many of them small-time traders from the 
Ikeja district of northern Lagos where Abiola lives, were 
holding a demonstration Monday when police intervened, firing in 
their direction and wounding seven, the committee said in a 
statement signed by its national secretary Segun Jegede. There 
was no independent confirmation of the incident. Abiola, a 
millionaire tycoon, was arrested on Thursday after declaring 
himself president, a year after the military annulled 
presidential elections he was widely held to have won. 

</TEXT>

